{"address": "1150 Coast Village Rd, Ste E", "attributes": {"Ambience": null, "BusinessParking": {"garage": false, "lot": false, "street": true, "valet": false, "validated": false}, "Music": null, "OutdoorSeating": null, "RestaurantsGoodForGroups": null, "RestaurantsReservations": null, "RestaurantsTakeOut": null, "WiFi": null}, "business_stars": 4.5, "categories": "Restaurants, Bakeries, Food", "city": "Montecito", "hours": {"Friday": "9:0-17:0", "Monday": "9:0-17:0", "Thursday": "9:0-17:0", "Tuesday": "9:0-17:0", "Wednesday": "9:0-17:0"}, "name": "Montecito Confections", "review_info": [{"review_date": "2014-08-14 04:36:40", "review_stars": 5.0, "review_text": "Ordered a white cake with buttercream. When I placed the order they suggested a light lemon cream filling which I went with. It was beyond perfect. Light fluffy buttercream, moist cake, and the filling was a perfect match up. Yep, I will be back!"}, {"review_date": "2014-08-07 19:34:34", "review_stars": 5.0, "review_text": "Katie baked the wedding cake of my dreams. It came out exactly as I wanted and was delicious. We had three tiers: two were red velvet and one was vanilla custard cake with fresh raspberries. I am very happy with our decision to choose her."}, {"review_date": "2014-05-09 15:00:38", "review_stars": 5.0, "review_text": "Katie Teall is an ANGEL!!!  I made a wedding cake for the daughter of a very close High School friend and the Fondant I bought (FondArt) was horrible.  I spent about 7 hours kneading it and rolling it, and no matter what I did when I covered a tier of the cake it cracked.  I was so stressed that decided to go to Montecito Confections to see if I could buy Fondant there.  I got there and asked Katie Teall the sweet adorable, British owner if she could help me.  she explained that she sold the store and the rest of her Fondant was for the last 15 wedding cakes that she had to deliver during the summer.  She must have seen my face of stress, exhaustion, just lost, and asked:  How big is your cake?  I told her and she said:  Do you want me to cover it in Fondant for you?  I jumped to hug her and kiss her and hug her and kissed her some more.

I came home and the mother of the bride carried the bottom tier and we went back to Montecito Confections to be saved by Katie.  We arrived and she said where is the rest of the cake?  I did not want to take advantage so we just took the biggest tier.  She said:  Bring it!

Home we went after hugging Katie and kissing her some more and got help and left with two more tiers.  Katie my angel covered the three tiers!!! She was my angel.  The mother of the bride broke in tears, I guess she was worried that I was never going to serve the wedding cake.  These were tears of relief!  We ended up having the most beautiful cake and thanks to Katie.  Katie also build the cake, putting all three tiers together.  Then explained to me how to decorate it.  She told me to get a photo of the container of her fondant because she had tried all the different brands and that was the best of them all.  She said that mine was impossible to work with since it was too dry!  Katie is a walking ANGEL.  I love her, love her and love her.  All the kisses and hugs are not enough to thank her for saving the wedding cake and so much more."}], "state": "CA"}

{"address": "938 Embarcadero Del Nrte", "attributes": {"Ambience": {"casual": true, "classy": false, "divey": false, "hipster": false, "intimate": false, "romantic": false, "touristy": false, "trendy": false, "upscale": false}, "BusinessParking": {"garage": false, "lot": false, "street": true, "valet": false, "validated": false}, "Music": null, "OutdoorSeating": true, "RestaurantsGoodForGroups": true, "RestaurantsReservations": false, "RestaurantsTakeOut": true, "WiFi": "free"}, "business_stars": 4.0, "categories": "Sandwiches, Restaurants, Burgers", "city": "Goleta", "hours": null, "name": "Javan's", "review_info": [{"review_date": "2014-02-25 06:54:05", "review_stars": 5.0, "review_text": "Sigh ... Javan's is no more :'(  I miss it already."}, {"review_date": "2013-09-10 00:43:52", "review_stars": 5.0, "review_text": "It perplexes me that this place is always so empty. Honestly it is the best food in IV without a doubt and it's because the owners double as the cooks and are invested in the overall quality of their ingredients and product. They are always entertaining and you could learn a thing or two from just conversing with them during your lunch. Consider helping out this humble mom and pop shop before heading to a big franchise restaurant because they do not compromise anything in their menu and are competitively priced compared to the rest of IV. 

I would recommend the Tuna sandwich for it's delicious combination of dressings and tastiness of the fish. Every bite is savory and leaves you wanting more. You can't go wrong with any of the sandwiches really though."}, {"review_date": "2013-09-09 04:07:36", "review_stars": 4.0, "review_text": "The owners of this place should seriously consider investing in a good quality sign for out front.  Currently they have an unlit vinyl sign so the place is basically unnoticeable, especially at night.  I bet they would really see business improve if they weren't cheap about the sign.

Good sandwiches and chili though."}], "state": "CA"}

{"address": "4020 Calle Real", "attributes": {"Ambience": {"casual": true, "classy": false, "divey": false, "hipster": false, "intimate": false, "romantic": false, "touristy": false, "trendy": false, "upscale": false}, "BusinessParking": {"garage": false, "lot": true, "street": false, "valet": false, "validated": false}, "Music": null, "OutdoorSeating": false, "RestaurantsGoodForGroups": true, "RestaurantsReservations": true, "RestaurantsTakeOut": true, "WiFi": "no"}, "business_stars": 4.0, "categories": "Japanese, Restaurants", "city": "Santa Barbara", "hours": {"Friday": "17:30-21:30", "Monday": "17:30-21:30", "Saturday": "17:30-21:30", "Thursday": "17:30-21:30", "Tuesday": "17:30-21:30", "Wednesday": "17:30-21:30"}, "name": "Itsuki Restaurant", "review_info": [{"review_date": "2015-05-25 20:54:35", "review_stars": 2.0, "review_text": "Absolutely disappointing. As a matter of fact, this experience was so disappointing it caused me to take time out of my very busy life to write my first review ever. 

I'm someone who is happy when there is quantity. So I spend $60 here thinking that should do a good job filling me up (I order the 25$ sashimi bowl and 2 rolls) and I did not get filled up. The sashimi itself disappointed me as well due to the low quantity of cuts compared to kyoto's 25$ bowl. In addition, the fish itself I thought was less fresh. The 2 rolls were also small in comparison to Kyoto's. I'm never coming here again. Man I could have gotten 10 chipotle burrito's with those $60...."}, {"review_date": "2013-04-23 19:18:42", "review_stars": 5.0, "review_text": "This is the best sushi in Santa Barbara, aside from maybe Arigato, which is absolutely not worth the money. Go, go, go!"}, {"review_date": "2013-01-09 23:59:06", "review_stars": 3.0, "review_text": "The restaurant has located to the Camino Real Marketplace area (actually, more like near Pacific Oaks) in Goleta, where Baja Fresh used to be. The ambiance is *totally* different. It's become a big business. They're still getting the hang of how to serve so many people, and seem always to be apologizing for slow service, when it's actually about the same as other places. 

The food was not great the first few times I went, but the last time...yum...they were back on their game. It's worth a try!"}], "state": "CA"}
